1
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:35,600
<i>Miss Yollada, you've aged quite a bit.</i>

2
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:37,840
<i>It's been a long time, Hong.</i>

3
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:40,320
<i>Her name is Mam Yollada,</i>
<i>owner of M Power Group,</i>

4
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,680
<i>an investment company on the surface.</i>

5
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:45,720
But in reality, it's a pyramid scheme.

6
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:47,560
<i>Why did you choose these eight people?</i>

7
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:49,440
<i>They look like con artists</i>
<i>you can't trust.</i>

8
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:53,400
<i>But to me, each of them is honest</i>
<i>about their own feelings.</i>

9
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:56,240
<i>They're the most trustworthy people.</i>

10
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,680
<i>It's good to see you all again.</i>

11
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,400
<i>Mam is a lonely woman</i>

12
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,920
who likes young guys.

13
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,680
<i>We need to send the person</i>
<i>who best fits her type</i>

14
00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:06,200
<i>to win her over</i>

15
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,800
<i>and get access to her money.</i>

16
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:09,720
<i>Don't they realize</i>
<i>they're about to be scammed?</i>

17
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:11,360
All because of greed, right, Ris?

18
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,040
You really think so?

19
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,440
If you were mindful

20
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:17,200
and not blinded by greed, couldn't you see

21
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,800
they're just selling a dream?

22
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:22,600
Who would believe
a small investment gives huge returns?

23
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,960
Totally crazy.

24
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,360
Is there anyone who hasn't registered yet?

25
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,880
The event will start in 15 minutes.

26
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:32,120
For those who have already registered,

27
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,120
please proceed inside.

28
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,000
Why does Admin
have to make us do stuff like this?

29
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,400
Stop complaining.

30
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,800
The more we know about Mam,

31
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:44,120
the easier it'll be
for Phayak to get the job done.

32
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,560
Come on, let's get inside.

33
00:02:45,640 --> 00:02:46,480
Hurry up.

34
00:03:09,480 --> 00:03:11,400
Many people have asked

35
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:14,160
if the "M" in M Power

36
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:16,000
stands for my name.

37
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:18,280
Actually, the "M"

38
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,480
means much more to me.

39
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:25,320
Money, Multiply, and Miracle.

40
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,160
It represents the power

41
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,520
to make your money

42
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:32,920
grow exponentially, almost magically.

43
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:42,280
And another "M"
that's very meaningful to me

44
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:45,240
is Members.

45
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,400
That's all of you

46
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:49,760
who have trusted me all along.

47
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,320
It's been proven

48
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:53,960
through the passive income

49
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:57,280
that flows steadily
into everyone's accounts.

50
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,400
It proves

51
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:01,200
that money

52
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:04,160
can work for you,

53
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:06,880
even while you're asleep.

54
00:04:13,600 --> 00:04:16,519
All of this proves

55
00:04:16,600 --> 00:04:18,680
that our company

56
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:22,120
can give everyone
more than you ever imagined.

57
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,040
She's insanely good at talking.

58
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:32,320
And for all the new investors here today,

59
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:35,800
could everyone raise your hands for me?

60
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:42,200
Everyone came here today

61
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:45,480
because you want to change your lives.

62
00:04:46,160 --> 00:04:48,280
Clench your fists tightly.

63
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,360
Because that means

64
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,600
you're holding an important opportunity

65
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,160
to change your life.

66
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:58,480
Can you say it out loud?

67
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,800
The reason you came here today,

68
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:02,360
what is it that you want?

69
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:05,880
Rich! Rich! Rich!

70
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,360
One more time?

71
00:05:07,440 --> 00:05:10,960
Rich! Rich! Rich!

72
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,680
If we don't act fast,
more people are going to get hurt.

73
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,760
Sorry.

74
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:54,360
-Are you okay?
-No, I'm fine.

75
00:06:00,520 --> 00:06:01,600
Gusjang?

76
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,640
Angpao? Wow, long time no see!

77
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,600
Hello.

78
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:17,280
Angpao, you came to the seminar too?

79
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,120
Yes.

80
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,920
Why haven't I ever seen you before?
Is this your first time?

81
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,480
Are you part of a group already?

82
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:28,400
No, no group. I'm just trying it out.

83
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:31,200
Oh, just trying it out.

84
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,640
If that's all,

85
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:41,880
I'll excuse myself. I have a meeting
with the others in my group.

86
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,040
Okay.

87
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,400
Bye.

88
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,360
Who was that?

89
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:58,640
Gusjang, my first love.

90
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,480
First love?

91
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:05,720
No wonder you're so embarrassed.

92
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,280
It's not like that.

93
00:07:08,880 --> 00:07:12,200
I don't even know
if I can call her my first love.

94
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:16,560
I secretly liked her
all through high school.

95
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,920
I don't think she even knew I liked her.

96
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,800
How could I not know?

97
00:07:31,280 --> 00:07:33,240
-Hi there.
-Hi.

98
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:36,640
I just realized
I forgot to get your Line ID.

99
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,120
-Line?
-We should grab a meal sometime.

100
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,520
Give me your QR code.

101
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,240
QR…

102
00:07:50,320 --> 00:07:54,160
-Open Line.
-Line…

103
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:04,160
We got a lot of new investors
from today's seminar.

104
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,560
They're just small fry.

105
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:12,760
I really have to apologize about Peak.

106
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:16,280
I'll quickly find
some bigger investors for you.

107
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,720
Don't waste your time.

108
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:21,640
What do you mean?

109
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:25,000
If you can't help me,

110
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:28,120
just stay out of it.
I'll handle it myself.

111
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,720
Yes.

112
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,840
Mam is starting
to take an interest in Mr. Anderson.

113
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,280
The next step

114
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,520
is to do whatever it takes

115
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,480
to make Mam fall in love with
and trust you,

116
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,280
so you can access her financial accounts.

117
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,080
Wait a minute.

118
00:09:20,400 --> 00:09:23,120
Hold on. Why do I feel like

119
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:26,280
everyone's putting all their hopes on me?
I can't handle this.

120
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:29,600
Because no one
can do this better than you.

121
00:09:29,680 --> 00:09:31,760
Yak, damn it.

122
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:34,080
You used to be a total Casanova.

123
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,680
How can you not handle
something this simple?

124
00:09:35,760 --> 00:09:36,880
Hey.

125
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:39,440
That's true.

126
00:09:40,040 --> 00:09:41,640
But that was a long time ago.

127
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:43,960
By the way,

128
00:09:44,040 --> 00:09:46,360
if I do that, will you be okay with it?

129
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:49,360
Work is work, personal life is personal.

130
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,400
I'll be totally fine

131
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,040
if you make Mam

132
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,920
fall head over heels for you.

133
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,320
I really don't want to do this.

134
00:09:58,080 --> 00:10:01,720
And this is
all of Mam's personal information

135
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,480
that everyone helped gather.

136
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:06,440
It'll make your mission much easier.

137
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:09,640
Are you a beauty or a devil?

138
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:11,520
You want me to memorize all of this?

139
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,120
I can't do it.

140
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:16,360
Don't worry. We'll feed you

141
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,400
every single piece of information

142
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,440
through the earpiece.

143
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:25,120
Oh. Okay, then I'll take the job.

144
00:10:26,920 --> 00:10:27,920
Everyone.

145
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:33,760
Don't you think
what we're doing is too much?

146
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:38,760
Tricking her into loving him
and then destroying her…

147
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,240
I think it's too cruel.

148
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:41,240
Chen.

149
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:44,280
Everything we've done so far,

150
00:10:44,360 --> 00:10:46,720
it's to help people Mam has scammed.

151
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:50,320
Those people have loved ones
they need to take care of too.

152
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:53,360
If we can take down Mam's pyramid scheme,

153
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,680
we can help thousands more.

154
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,400
-I think it's worth it.
-Yeah.

155
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,440
Well said.

156
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,080
So,

157
00:11:02,160 --> 00:11:04,080
you have to make Mam

158
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:08,480
fall for you so hard,
she can't think. Got it?

159
00:11:09,280 --> 00:11:10,240
Got it.

160
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:11,520
Don't worry.

161
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,440
This is my specialty.

162
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,920
Who's really benefiting from this?

163
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:24,320
What are you complaining about, Chen?
I don't get it.

164
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,840
It's the plan where everyone

165
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:29,280
tricks Miss Mam into falling in love
and then destroys her.

166
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,600
I just don't like it.

167
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:35,040
Hey. You're still hung up on this?

168
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:38,200
Well, if she committed fraud,

169
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:40,920
she should face
the consequences for that fraud.

170
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,600
We shouldn't go
and completely break her heart like this.

171
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:44,920
You're overthinking it.

172
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,280
Hey, Koh.

173
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,120
Listen to me and think about this.

174
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,040
If you commit one wrongdoing,

175
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:53,760
but have to take responsibility
for something else, is that right?

176
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:56,320
And it's not just that.

177
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:59,000
The people who love and care about them,

178
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:01,000
their hearts break too.

179
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,400
Where should we eat?

180
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:05,640
You choose, Pao.

181
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,720
Me? Barbecue?

182
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:10,000
-Sure.
-Yeah.

183
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,000
Okay.

184
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,440
Honestly,

185
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,920
there are two things that still bother me.

186
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:23,480
First, I want to know if he's still alive.

187
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,680
And the other thing?

188
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,640
I want to know

189
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,200
that day at the train station…

190
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,760
I'm sure

191
00:12:34,840 --> 00:12:37,360
he saw the train leaving.

192
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:41,320
He heard me calling out to him.

193
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:46,440
But how could he

194
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:51,000
bring himself to leave me behind?

195
00:12:54,520 --> 00:12:55,480
Koh.

196
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,200
Koh.

197
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:58,920
Are you even listening to me?

198
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,880
Hey, guys.

199
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,440
Where should I drop you off?
Near or far, the price is fair.

200
00:13:05,520 --> 00:13:08,040
Just at the car watch in the alley.
No need to charge them.

201
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:14,080
Chen, you go with them.

202
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:17,200
I'll walk. I'm planning to stay out
a while longer. See you.

203
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,440
Hey, Koh. We have work tomorrow.

204
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,280
Stay out longer? Hey, man.

205
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:24,800
Koh!

206
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:28,160
What's wrong with him?

207
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,880
-Hello, Miss Mam.
-Hello, Miss Mam.

208
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,600
Someone is here
requesting to see you urgently.

209
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,160
Who? I didn't schedule anyone.

210
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:49,840
But he insists
that you'll definitely want to meet him.

211
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,520
Do you know

212
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:24,720
what I feel when I look at the city

213
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,160
from a high-rise like this?

214
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:29,480
I feel freedom.

215
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:33,240
And my free spirit

216
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,240
has brought me

217
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:39,200
to meet you, Miss Mam.

218
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,640
Who are you?

219
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:47,960
I should be asking you the same thing.
Who are you?

220
00:14:59,920 --> 00:15:02,200
Oh, your hands are full. Let me help.

221
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,240
Never mind.

222
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,760
Alright.

223
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:09,600
I'm Peter. Did you have an appointment
with Miss Mam?

224
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:12,000
I had an appointment with Miss Mam.

225
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:16,240
Who the heck is Peter?

226
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:17,800
Peter is one of Mam's close aides.

227
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:19,080
He's a real troublemaker.

228
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,160
You should find a way
to shake him off quickly.

229
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,320
Acknowledged.

230
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,080
Acknowledged what?

231
00:15:25,040 --> 00:15:27,720
Oh. Acknowledged that your name is Peter.

232
00:15:29,800 --> 00:15:32,120
But looking at Miss Mam's schedule,

233
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,600
you didn't make an appointment with her.

234
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:39,640
Did you check?

235
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:45,200
Oh, I didn't make an appointment,

236
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,880
but she wanted to see me, so I came.

237
00:15:52,240 --> 00:15:54,280
Mr. Anderson!

238
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,280
Miss Mam!

239
00:15:59,120 --> 00:16:01,120
<i>Ciao! Ciao!</i>

240
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,720
Oh! <i>Ciao!</i>

241
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:08,920
How did you know I work here?

242
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:11,840
Oh, I knew. Finding you

243
00:16:11,920 --> 00:16:15,000
was never difficult for me.

244
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:21,800
Do you have any business here?

245
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:24,960
Oh, today

246
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:29,080
I came to keep the promise I made to you.

247
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:31,240
I want to treat you to a meal to thank you

248
00:16:31,320 --> 00:16:34,840
for the help you gave me before.

249
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,320
May I know if you're free?

250
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:41,240
-She's not free!
-I'm--

251
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,560
At noon, she has a lunch appointment
with the deputy assistant.

252
00:16:47,680 --> 00:16:48,680
Oh.

253
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:53,320
But Peter, you can go in my place.

254
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:57,440
This is a matter that requires
your decision, Miss Mam.

255
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:04,200
Then Peter, just decide for me.

256
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:13,800
It's almost time for the appointment.

257
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:16,760
If you don't leave now,
the traffic will be bad.

258
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:17,839
Yeah?

259
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,200
Alright.

260
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:34,360
Nice to meet you,

261
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,160
-Peter's clear.
-Great!

262
00:18:05,240 --> 00:18:06,560
Confirm with Chen.

263
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:10,160
Hello, Chen?

264
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:13,120
Phayak is taking Mam to lunch.
Are you ready over there?

265
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:17,280
We've got a little problem over here.

266
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:20,520
The restaurant's closed?

267
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:24,320
Yeah. Chen said someone
booked out the entire place today.

268
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:27,320
Why are you telling me this only now?
We're almost at the restaurant.

269
00:18:34,320 --> 00:18:36,560
Don't jerk the car around.

270
00:18:36,640 --> 00:18:38,080
Yeah, drive carefully.

271
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:46,960
AH FU ROAST DUCK

272
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:07,800
Well, you did your homework.

273
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:09,440
You knew this is my favorite restaurant.

274
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:15,160
Wow, I didn't know that before,
so I must have a sixth sense.

275
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:17,920
After you.

276
00:19:31,880 --> 00:19:33,440
We're sorry.

277
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:36,600
Today, the restaurant has been booked
for a private event.

278
00:19:36,680 --> 00:19:38,520
We'll be open again this evening.

279
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,080
Someone booked the whole restaurant?

280
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:49,000
In that case, I guess
we'll have to find somewhere else to eat.

281
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:54,320
But I was really looking forward
to eating here.

282
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,440
What should we do?

283
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:59,280
Oh, Mam!

284
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:11,560
Boss Lee, hello.

285
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:15,160
So it was you
who booked the restaurant today,

286
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,720
which is why I couldn't eat here.

287
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,800
It's okay. You can eat here.

288
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,040
The person who made the reservation
canceled on me.

289
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,280
I've already ordered a lot.

290
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:30,280
Is that alright, boss?

291
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:32,880
Of course. By the way, who's this?

292
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:36,000
I forgot to introduce him.

293
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,760
This is Mr. Anderson.

294
00:20:38,360 --> 00:20:40,320
And this is Boss Lee.

295
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:44,480
He's one of Thailand's
top diamond merchants.

296
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:50,160
Oh, you're in the diamond business
in Italy too, right?

297
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,640
Great. It's good to know each other.

298
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:59,000
Let's go inside
I've ordered a lot of food.

299
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:01,920
-Come on, don't worry.
-Okay, boss.

300
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,520
It's my treat today.

301
00:21:11,600 --> 00:21:14,320
This is bad. We just ran
into a real diamond merchant.

302
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:18,120
There he is. Boss Lee Lertpetch,

303
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:20,160
owner of Lee Gem Luxury,

304
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:23,320
one of Thailand's top diamond dealers.

305
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:26,120
This guy also invested in M Power.

306
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:28,000
I bet he's trying to flirt with Mam.

307
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:31,960
I think this time,
the plan is definitely going to fail.

308
00:21:38,080 --> 00:21:39,040
<i>Ciao!</i>

309
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:43,920
That's quite a ring, Mr. Anderson.

310
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:49,960
This is Mr. Anderson's family ring
from Italy.

311
00:21:50,040 --> 00:21:51,200
Is that so?

312
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:53,680
I'm not familiar with it.

313
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:55,880
What do you mean, boss?

314
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:59,160
The Anderson family is quite well known.

315
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:07,720
Excuse me for a moment.
A client is calling.

316
00:22:07,800 --> 00:22:09,960
Oh, sure.

317
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:11,240
Hello.

318
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,160
May I take another look at the ring?

319
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,640
That should be enough, right?

320
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:27,040
Finished yet? I'm starting to get hungry.

321
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,160
It's a beautiful ring.

322
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:35,640
That must be a rare diamond.
No wonder it's a family heirloom.

323
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,680
You've got a sharp eye, Mr. Lee.

324
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:45,360
Please, this way.

325
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:47,080
I'm getting hungry.

326
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:51,480
Braised chicken with winter melon
and preserved lime.

327
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:52,640
I'll serve you.

328
00:22:54,520 --> 00:22:56,360
You enjoy cooking, don't you?

329
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:06,200
I mean, this braised chicken
with winter melon and preserved lime.

330
00:23:10,920 --> 00:23:13,200
I do. I like braised chicken,
braised duck,

331
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:15,440
I like everything.

332
00:23:15,520 --> 00:23:17,240
And you like cooking people up, don't you?

333
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,400
About that ring,

334
00:23:24,480 --> 00:23:26,960
I could tell at a glance it's fake.

335
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:29,360
You can buy something like that
all over Sampeng.

336
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:34,600
What do you mean? I've never heard
of Sampeng. Never been there.

337
00:23:36,560 --> 00:23:38,320
And do you know what this is?

338
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:41,960
A gun.

339
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,480
A gun.

340
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:50,480
We have to do something,
or Phayak's in serious trouble.

341
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,680
Koh, where did you go?

342
00:23:56,680 --> 00:24:00,040
Look at that. Your men ran off
over something this small.

343
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:01,600
You're nothing but a petty thief!

344
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:05,800
Hold on! Why are you pointing a gun at me?

345
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:07,880
Where did Koh go?

346
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:10,280
I don't know. I've tried calling him,
but he won't answer.

347
00:24:12,040 --> 00:24:14,200
Are you going to tell Mam
the truth yourself,

348
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:16,440
or should I shoot you first
and let you tell her afterward?

349
00:24:17,720 --> 00:24:19,120
I'm back!

350
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:26,640
Wow, braised chicken
with winter melon and preserved lime!

351
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:28,080
It's my favorite.

352
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:30,120
-Hey, Mam.
-Yes?

353
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:33,360
I think Mr. Anderson
has something to tell you.

354
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:41,960
Is something wrong?

355
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,400
About the family ring.

356
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:45,160
Go ahead, Mr. Anderson.

357
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,880
What about the family ring, Mr. Anderson?

358
00:24:50,480 --> 00:24:51,520
Well…

359
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,160
Don't mess with me! Let go!

360
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:05,760
That damn Mam! Where is she?

361
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:09,520
-Mam, you bitch!
-Hey! What are you doing?

362
00:25:18,040 --> 00:25:19,560
What do we do now?

363
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:22,720
You have to fight Chen.

364
00:25:22,800 --> 00:25:25,400
Wait. Not yet.

365
00:25:28,520 --> 00:25:29,480
Miss Mam!

366
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:33,440
Get out of here first. I'll handle this.

367
00:25:33,520 --> 00:25:34,800
Okay.

368
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:42,000
Mam!

369
00:25:42,080 --> 00:25:43,360
So this is where you've been, huh?

370
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:45,680
Who are you?

371
00:25:45,760 --> 00:25:48,760
Who am I? I'm one of your victims!

372
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,600
You stole my money.

373
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:53,040
Hey! Don't move!

374
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,160
Don't move?

375
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:57,960
Don't move, huh?

376
00:25:58,040 --> 00:25:59,000
Boss Lee!

377
00:26:04,040 --> 00:26:07,760
I think they're up to something.

378
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,560
Hey, Mam!

379
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:11,840
Don't come near me.

380
00:26:11,920 --> 00:26:14,040
Don't do anything! I'm scared!

381
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:15,200
Don't come near me!

382
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:17,800
Give me my money!

383
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:25,920
Stop hurting this cute, harmless woman
who can't even defend herself.

384
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,960
Let's settle this one-on-one.

385
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:48,200
How dare you hurt my man and Miss Mam!

386
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:51,840
Miss Mam, go find somewhere safe.

387
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:55,240
Okay.

388
00:27:05,960 --> 00:27:07,640
You wanna die, huh, punk?

389
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:09,920
Fine. I'll show you.

390
00:27:23,640 --> 00:27:26,760
That really hurts.
Just hold it there. I'll twist it myself.

391
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:28,280
Okay.

392
00:27:30,640 --> 00:27:31,880
-Is this okay?
-Yeah.

393
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,200
Okay.

394
00:27:34,400 --> 00:27:35,680
This is not okay!

395
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,480
Wait!

396
00:27:43,640 --> 00:27:46,840
Remember, don't mess with Miss Mam again,

397
00:27:46,920 --> 00:27:49,560
or you'll end up like this.

398
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:51,280
I'm sorry!

399
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:41,320
Today's been such a strange day.

400
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:46,160
I haven't been this happy in a long time.

401
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:55,440
Can I borrow your phone for a second?

402
00:28:58,840 --> 00:29:01,160
We don't have each other's numbers yet.

403
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:04,040
Right.

404
00:29:10,720 --> 00:29:13,400
From now on, you can call me this.

405
00:29:25,720 --> 00:29:27,840
In Italian, it means "treasure".

406
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:30,720
And in another sense,
it also means "darling".

407
00:29:30,800 --> 00:29:33,600
I told you to call me Tesoro.

408
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:40,400
Like babe, darling,
or something like that.

409
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:44,080
What is it?

410
00:29:55,360 --> 00:30:00,360
Looks like our Ms. Mam
is totally falling for Mr. Anderson.

411
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,720
GUSJANG

412
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:12,400
FREE TOMORROW? MISS YOU. WANT TO SEE YOU.

413
00:30:14,520 --> 00:30:16,200
-What is it, Pao?
-Huh?

414
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:19,360
Nothing.

415
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:23,400
-Keeping secrets now, huh?
-No. Hey, what is this?

416
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:57,040
I'm really glad you messaged me on Line.

417
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:00,440
I missed you, so I wanted to see you.

418
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:02,480
How have you been, Angpao? Doing well?

419
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:06,760
Yeah, I'm doing fine.

420
00:31:07,720 --> 00:31:10,000
Oh, I…

421
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,520
I brought something for you.

422
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:19,360
Hey, you didn't have to. What's this?

423
00:31:22,040 --> 00:31:23,040
Wow.

424
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,400
Well…

425
00:31:30,240 --> 00:31:37,120
I remembered that you wanted
to be a ballerina.

426
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:40,280
So I bought this for you.

427
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:44,240
Do you like it?

428
00:31:56,880 --> 00:31:58,000
I do.

429
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:07,320
Actually, I asked you to meet today

430
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:11,040
because I wanted to invite you
to invest with my group.

431
00:32:11,800 --> 00:32:13,240
They say that

432
00:32:13,320 --> 00:32:16,320
if several people invest together,
the returns are even higher.

433
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:17,960
Interested?

434
00:32:23,880 --> 00:32:25,160
Gusjang.

435
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:27,760
I think…

436
00:32:29,360 --> 00:32:30,920
you should pull your money out.

437
00:32:32,120 --> 00:32:34,800
-Why?
-I heard

438
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:39,000
this company is a pyramid scheme.

439
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:42,680
No way, Angpao.
I've been getting returns the whole time.

440
00:32:42,760 --> 00:32:44,520
That's how it starts.

441
00:32:45,360 --> 00:32:47,080
Once they can't recruit
new members anymore,

442
00:32:47,920 --> 00:32:50,840
they'll shut everything down
and disappear. Trust me.

443
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,000
I don't believe you, Angpao.

444
00:32:58,520 --> 00:33:01,560
If you're not interested, just say so.

445
00:33:03,320 --> 00:33:04,400
I'll go.

446
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:08,800
No, Gusjang. Gus.

447
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:14,120
Gusjang, listen to me.

448
00:33:15,960 --> 00:33:17,280
Your family is rich, right?

449
00:33:17,880 --> 00:33:19,480
You don't need to do this.

450
00:33:25,320 --> 00:33:26,840
My family's bankrupt!

451
00:33:28,280 --> 00:33:30,160
My dad is drowning in debt!

452
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,720
My mom left us!

453
00:33:34,360 --> 00:33:36,120
I can't even go to school anymore.

454
00:33:36,200 --> 00:33:39,720
I had to drop out and work to earn money.

455
00:33:43,440 --> 00:33:46,800
Keep the music box, Angpao.
I don't want it.

456
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:48,920
Gusjang.

457
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:06,000
-MISS YOU
-I MISS YOU MORE

458
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:07,240
DON'T FORGET TO EAT, HONEY
I'M WORRIED ABOUT YOU

459
00:34:07,320 --> 00:34:08,360
-YOU TOO, DON'T OVERWORK YOURSELF
-YES, HONEY

460
00:34:10,280 --> 00:34:13,159
-SILLY, I HAVE TO WORK NOW. MISS YOU
-I'LL PICK YOU UP AFTER WORK

461
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:18,280
-I MISS YOU, MY TESORO
-CAN I JUST LEAVE WORK RIGHT NOW?

462
00:34:23,639 --> 00:34:26,440
Miss Mam, we need to talk.

463
00:34:28,440 --> 00:34:29,320
About what?

464
00:34:29,400 --> 00:34:32,280
Why did you cancel the appointment
with the investors I arranged?

465
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:35,679
-And why does it matter?
-Why are you doing this?

466
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:46,560
I'm busy.

467
00:34:46,639 --> 00:34:48,679
Are you serious about running
this company or not?

468
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:57,760
Who do you think you are,
raising your voice at me?

469
00:34:59,760 --> 00:35:01,240
Get out.

470
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,400
I don't want to see you again.

471
00:35:06,520 --> 00:35:07,800
Were you planning to trick Anderson,

472
00:35:09,360 --> 00:35:11,800
or did you actually fall for him?

473
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:41,440
-What's going on?
-Mr. Peter, one of the members

474
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:44,200
is causing a scene about not getting
the money again. Should I deal with him?

475
00:35:46,720 --> 00:35:48,160
Leave him alone.

476
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,560
Is that really okay?

477
00:35:53,240 --> 00:35:54,440
She'll learn

478
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:58,840
what happens when I'm not around.

479
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:14,880
How's it going, Mr. Anderson
and his big, beefy bodyguard?

480
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:20,960
-Tired yet?
-Not at all, sis.

481
00:36:21,040 --> 00:36:23,040
When those two spark,

482
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:26,040
they disappear and leave me behind.

483
00:36:26,120 --> 00:36:29,680
Now they're even going
to the beach together.

484
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,520
Everything I do,

485
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:33,320
I do for all of you.

486
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:36,320
Can I ask for one thing? Next time,
can we rehearse the fight scenes first?

487
00:36:36,400 --> 00:36:38,400
Going freestyle like that,
I feel like I'm the one getting hurt.

488
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,360
Not my fault. This guy!

489
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:42,800
-He's the mastermind.
-That's enough.

490
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:45,560
And Peter? Did you get him
out of the way yet?

491
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:48,080
Oh, don't worry about that.

492
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:51,440
I convinced Mam to send him
out of the office this morning.

493
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:54,000
No idea where he is now.
Probably drunk and passed out somewhere.

494
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,640
Perfect.

495
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:58,840
Here's to the disaster heading Mam's way!

496
00:36:58,920 --> 00:37:00,520
-Cheers, Hong.
-Cheers!

497
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,480
Okay, men's.

498
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:41,320
Excuse me.

499
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:45,560
Take it.

500
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,080
You guys!

501
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:52,880
Sorry. You'll never get the chance
to tell Mam about this.

502
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:54,760
Sorry, bro.

503
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:26,600
<i>Sorry, the number you dialed</i>
<i>cannot be reached.</i>

504
00:38:26,680 --> 00:38:27,920
PETER

505
00:38:29,360 --> 00:38:30,160
Honey.

506
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:34,320
What happened? What's wrong?
You look stressed.

507
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:36,400
Did I do something to upset you?

508
00:38:37,120 --> 00:38:40,920
Not at all. Maybe
I'm just a little stressed about work.

509
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:44,000
And Peter isn't answering my calls either.

510
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:47,360
What kind of employee is that?
He's a subordinate.

511
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:49,560
Why won't he answer his boss's calls?
That's not good at all.

512
00:38:49,640 --> 00:38:52,600
Maybe because

513
00:38:52,680 --> 00:38:54,400
I wasn't very nice to him the other day.

514
00:38:54,480 --> 00:38:56,080
Oh, honey.

515
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:02,920
-Go ahead, sis.
-Got him good.

516
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,640
Here's what we'll do.

517
00:39:04,720 --> 00:39:08,240
How about we stop by the office?
Maybe Peter's there.

518
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:12,040
It's okay, really. Let's just go.

519
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:14,840
-Yes.
-Okay.

520
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:30,000
I KNOW YOU'RE BETRAYING ME FOR ANDERSON
I WON'T LET YOU DO THAT

521
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:33,440
Honey, is everything okay?

522
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:35,440
I'm fine.

523
00:39:39,920 --> 00:39:44,800
Can I stop by the office for a moment?

524
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:48,520
Of course.

525
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:51,200
Go ahead.

526
00:39:52,600 --> 00:39:55,640
-I'll open the door for you.
-Thank you.

527
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:13,960
You can wait in the car.
I'll just go check on some documents.

528
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:19,040
-What's going on?
-I don't get it at all.

529
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:23,720
Miss Mam, is there some kind of event
happening at your office?

530
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:31,560
-What is this?
-It's so hot out.

531
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:34,320
<i>Breaking news.</i>

532
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:37,600
<i>Chaos is unfolding right now</i>
<i>outside the BEG Building.</i>

533
00:40:37,680 --> 00:40:39,320
-The BEG building?
-<i>A major office tower</i>

534
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:41,720
-That's your office, honey.
-<i>in central Bangkok.</i>

535
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:45,040
-Hey, Koh! Turn up the volume.
-<i>Sources have revealed</i>

536
00:40:45,120 --> 00:40:47,800
<i>that M Power,</i>

537
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:51,000
<i>a major investment company, is allegedly</i>
<i>operating as a pyramid scheme.</i>

538
00:40:51,080 --> 00:40:52,720
<i>Many victims have gathered</i>

539
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:55,000
<i>-In front of the office,</i>
-Are they working today?

540
00:40:55,080 --> 00:40:57,840
<i>demanding that Miss Mam Yollada,</i>

541
00:40:57,920 --> 00:41:01,360
<i>CEO of M Power Group, take responsibility.</i>

542
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:06,480
What did the reporter mean just now?

543
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:10,080
Tell me what's going on.

544
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,320
Yes, sir.

545
00:41:18,400 --> 00:41:21,320
-Calm down.
-How can I calm down? We're exhausted.

546
00:41:21,400 --> 00:41:23,400
The evidence is right here.

547
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:28,520
It's obviously a scam!

548
00:41:44,760 --> 00:41:48,240
-Well…
-You're hiding something from me, right?

549
00:41:48,320 --> 00:41:49,720
No, not at all.

550
00:41:49,800 --> 00:41:51,720
It's all just a misunderstanding.

551
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,600
You…

552
00:41:56,480 --> 00:41:58,440
You run a pyramid scheme, don't you?

553
00:41:58,520 --> 00:42:01,320
No, I don't. I really don't.

554
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:04,440
Honestly, I've never done
anything like that.

555
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:06,480
You have to tell me.

556
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:10,240
I don't care if it's a pyramid scheme
or anything else.

557
00:42:10,320 --> 00:42:12,880
You know why? Because…

558
00:42:14,680 --> 00:42:15,840
I love you.

559
00:42:19,240 --> 00:42:23,040
But love has to come with trust.

560
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:25,680
If you don't tell me what's going on,

561
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:28,840
I won't be able to help you, honey.

562
00:42:34,360 --> 00:42:35,600
Yes.

563
00:42:36,760 --> 00:42:39,480
It's all true.

564
00:42:41,520 --> 00:42:44,400
My company is a pyramid scheme.

565
00:42:45,400 --> 00:42:49,120
But I've been trying to shut it down,

566
00:42:49,200 --> 00:42:51,080
so we could run away and be together.

567
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:55,920
I know what I've done is wrong,

568
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:59,120
and I've been trying
to get out of it for a long time.

569
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:03,920
But… I mean…

570
00:43:05,720 --> 00:43:07,720
It's because of Peter.

571
00:43:07,800 --> 00:43:10,240
Peter forced me into all of this.

572
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:13,120
It was his plan from the very beginning.

573
00:43:13,200 --> 00:43:14,720
What do you mean?

574
00:43:17,400 --> 00:43:19,840
-Wait. Don't tell me.
-What?

575
00:43:20,960 --> 00:43:22,840
Could this whole thing
have been Peter's plan?

576
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:31,560
That's it! Now I know.

577
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:35,480
I know who leaked the story.

578
00:43:35,560 --> 00:43:38,400
Yes, it has to be Peter.

579
00:43:38,480 --> 00:43:40,080
He's angry with me.

580
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:42,800
He's angry because I slapped him that day.

581
00:43:43,960 --> 00:43:46,880
This is bad, Mam.

582
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:52,080
You know why? Peter knows everything
about your company.

583
00:43:52,800 --> 00:43:56,480
If he's the one who leaked the story,

584
00:43:56,560 --> 00:43:59,480
that means he's already pulled
the money out of the company.

585
00:44:05,280 --> 00:44:06,120
ENTER PIN

586
00:44:12,520 --> 00:44:13,880
The company's money is still there.

587
00:44:13,960 --> 00:44:16,800
Oh God, this isn't good. In that case,

588
00:44:16,880 --> 00:44:20,040
transfer all the money
to my account immediately.

589
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:22,360
Why?

590
00:44:23,040 --> 00:44:25,840
You have to trust me right now.

591
00:44:25,920 --> 00:44:27,400
Transfer it to me,

592
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:31,400
and we'll run away
and start a new life together.

593
00:44:32,240 --> 00:44:35,800
Well… I mean…

594
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:37,240
Just transfer it. Hurry up.

595
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:40,720
Quickly. We don't have time.

596
00:44:47,240 --> 00:44:49,920
Koh, Peter got away.

597
00:44:50,000 --> 00:44:52,880
-What?
-<i>Did she agree to transfer the money yet?</i>

598
00:44:52,960 --> 00:44:54,720
Transfer the money to my account.

599
00:44:57,520 --> 00:44:59,520
But I…

600
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:06,760
We'll get to start a new life together.

601
00:45:06,840 --> 00:45:08,880
-I think we need to hurry!
-Huh?

602
00:45:23,400 --> 00:45:25,400
Hurry! Transfer it now!

603
00:45:25,480 --> 00:45:27,000
-Well…
-Hurry!

604
00:45:27,080 --> 00:45:28,840
-I mean…
-Transfer it, Miss Mam!

605
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:32,160
Hand Miss Mam over
if you don't want to die!

606
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:35,000
-Miss Mam.
-Geez! What is this?

607
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,720
Hey, you bastard!

608
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:38,600
How could you do this to me?

609
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:41,760
Miss Mam, everything
was part of their plan.

610
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:44,640
Don't you dare touch Miss Mam!

611
00:45:45,440 --> 00:45:47,200
-Stop acting!
-Huh?

612
00:45:50,920 --> 00:45:52,040
Miss Mam.

613
00:45:52,720 --> 00:45:53,760
MY ACCOUNT, AVAILABLE BALANCE

614
00:45:53,840 --> 00:45:55,880
Good thing you haven't transferred
the money yet.

615
00:45:57,880 --> 00:45:59,520
What does this mean?

616
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:02,400
Hey, Mam! Don't listen to him!

617
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:04,960
That's enough, Uncle.

618
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:07,000
Our cover's blown.

619
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:09,240
Damn it.

620
00:46:11,120 --> 00:46:12,280
Will someone please tell me

621
00:46:12,960 --> 00:46:14,480
what's going on?

622
00:46:15,320 --> 00:46:17,800
Everything was part of their plan.

623
00:46:29,880 --> 00:46:31,960
They're trying to trick you
into transferring the money.

624
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:57,120
How's Peter doing?

625
00:46:57,680 --> 00:47:01,760
I just checked on him.
He still hasn't woken up yet.

626
00:47:01,840 --> 00:47:04,160
What do we do next, sis?

627
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:07,080
Angpao, how many times have we
gone over this? You never remember.

628
00:47:07,160 --> 00:47:10,440
You were supposed to lead people
to Mam's building. Did you do it yet?

629
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:15,720
The clearance sale to lure people
to the building? I already shared it.

630
00:47:16,320 --> 00:47:19,640
Look! Appliance clearance sale!
Up to 80% off!

631
00:47:19,720 --> 00:47:20,960
There's no such thing here.

632
00:47:21,040 --> 00:47:23,040
There isn't even
an electronics company in this building.

633
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:25,000
-But here's the proof!
-Look, see?

634
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:27,640
-There's no such thing.
-So that means

635
00:47:27,720 --> 00:47:29,080
it's Risa's turn next, right?

636
00:47:29,160 --> 00:47:31,560
-<i>Yes.</i>
-Breaking news.

637
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:35,680
Chaos is unfolding right now
outside the BEG building.

638
00:47:35,760 --> 00:47:37,080
Here, check this!

639
00:47:37,160 --> 00:47:40,040
<i>Sources have revealed</i>

640
00:47:40,120 --> 00:47:42,800
<i>that M Power,</i>

641
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:46,160
<i>a major investment company, is allegedly</i>
<i>operating as a pyramid scheme.</i>

642
00:47:46,920 --> 00:47:48,040
And next,

643
00:47:48,120 --> 00:47:51,760
I'll use Peter's phone to text Mam,

644
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:55,840
so she'll think he betrayed her.

645
00:47:56,680 --> 00:47:59,240
Hey, keep an eye on him.

646
00:47:59,320 --> 00:48:01,680
Don't let him escape. If he gets away,
our whole plan falls apart.

647
00:48:01,760 --> 00:48:03,000
Whoa, sis.

648
00:48:03,080 --> 00:48:05,800
His hands are cuffed.

649
00:48:05,880 --> 00:48:09,120
Unless he's crazy enough to break
his own fingers, there's no way out.

650
00:48:09,200 --> 00:48:11,200
What if he actually does?

651
00:48:43,640 --> 00:48:46,240
Hey! Stop!

652
00:48:46,320 --> 00:48:49,160
-What the hell, man?
-Let me borrow your phone. It's urgent.

653
00:48:49,240 --> 00:48:50,200
My phone?

654
00:48:51,040 --> 00:48:52,880
-Hurry up!
-Wait! One sec.

655
00:48:54,640 --> 00:48:55,800
Give me that.

656
00:48:58,840 --> 00:49:00,960
Send a car to pick me up. Now.

657
00:49:01,640 --> 00:49:03,400
They wanted you to think I betrayed you

658
00:49:04,160 --> 00:49:05,800
so you'd transfer the money to them.

659
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:10,240
Right, Mr. Anderson?

660
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:13,040
Wait, no.

661
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:14,960
It's Phayak.

662
00:49:40,480 --> 00:49:41,640
Get rid of him.

663
00:49:46,280 --> 00:49:47,400
Go!

664
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:49,400
Move!

665
00:50:13,200 --> 00:50:14,040
Get out!

666
00:50:15,800 --> 00:50:16,840
Go.

667
00:50:22,400 --> 00:50:23,360
Move.

668
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:25,600
Go!

669
00:50:30,520 --> 00:50:33,560
-Should I deal with them now?
-Take it easy.

670
00:50:39,720 --> 00:50:42,560
Let's play a little game first.

671
00:50:54,040 --> 00:50:55,320
Between the two of you…

672
00:50:58,000 --> 00:50:59,640
who's the bigger coward?

673
00:51:00,640 --> 00:51:02,280
I am.

674
00:51:05,880 --> 00:51:07,760
I'll give you both a chance.

675
00:51:08,840 --> 00:51:10,080
Take turns pulling the trigger.

676
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:14,800
But there's only one bullet.

677
00:51:17,680 --> 00:51:21,920
Whoever survives gets to live.
Fair enough?

678
00:51:23,960 --> 00:51:25,720
So who goes first?

679
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:29,600
I'll go first.

680
00:51:30,240 --> 00:51:31,960
Hey, how can you say that?

681
00:51:32,040 --> 00:51:33,720
Going first is a sacrifice.

682
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:35,760
Alright.

683
00:51:36,360 --> 00:51:38,280
No need to argue. You'll both get a turn.

684
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:45,040
You go first.

685
00:51:49,400 --> 00:51:51,360
If you don't shoot, you die too.

686
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:56,600
-Koh.
-Take it.

687
00:52:05,240 --> 00:52:06,280
Koh.

688
00:52:13,200 --> 00:52:14,760
Are you going to shoot or not?

689
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:18,240
Whoa, I'm outta here!

690
00:52:37,160 --> 00:52:38,960
You can try again next round.

691
00:52:52,720 --> 00:52:54,720
-Sorry, bro.
-Sorry for what?

692
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:29,320
Whoever doesn't get shot survives, right?

693
00:53:32,760 --> 00:53:34,080
Unbelievable.

694
00:53:35,200 --> 00:53:36,520
You guys are so selfish.

695
00:53:37,160 --> 00:53:38,480
I hope you keep your word.

696
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:42,480
Okay, I'll keep my promise…

697
00:53:44,720 --> 00:53:46,320
as long as you don't break the rules.

698
00:54:15,400 --> 00:54:18,680
It's done. I've sent men

699
00:54:18,760 --> 00:54:20,520
after the rest of them.

700
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:24,720
Don't worry.

701
00:54:24,800 --> 00:54:27,480
I already told Louis to take care of it.

702
00:54:30,240 --> 00:54:33,880
Are we still holding
the fundraising event next week?

703
00:54:37,040 --> 00:54:38,480
We have to.

704
00:54:38,560 --> 00:54:42,000
The system doesn't have enough money
to keep the payouts going.

705
00:54:42,080 --> 00:54:43,480
If this continues,

706
00:54:43,560 --> 00:54:45,800
the downline investors
will definitely sue us.

707
00:54:46,520 --> 00:54:47,640
That's why

708
00:54:47,720 --> 00:54:51,000
we need to bring in
as many big investors as possible,

709
00:54:51,720 --> 00:54:54,360
then shut everything down
and disappear again.

710
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:02,080
I think I know who we can target.

711
00:55:11,000 --> 00:55:13,200
Damn it! Hey!

712
00:55:13,280 --> 00:55:15,160
So we really can't do anything now?

713
00:55:15,240 --> 00:55:18,960
We just sit here and watch Mam
act like nothing happened?

714
00:55:20,120 --> 00:55:23,400
That's just how it is.
What else can we do, sis?

715
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:26,360
This is so frustrating!

716
00:55:26,440 --> 00:55:28,760
I knew this plan wouldn't work.

717
00:55:32,280 --> 00:55:36,080
I think we still have a chance.
We should wait a little longer.

718
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:39,440
I hate waiting. I hate losing to Mam!

719
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:42,280
MARK, PETER, PEAK

720
00:55:42,360 --> 00:55:45,360
Hey, can someone answer the phone?
It's driving me crazy!

721
00:55:45,440 --> 00:55:48,440
Mr. Peak's father is interested
in making a major investment with us.

722
00:55:48,520 --> 00:55:49,720
Who would've thought

723
00:55:49,800 --> 00:55:52,240
he'd come back
to swallow up his old target?

724
00:55:52,320 --> 00:55:56,000
<i>Hurry. I think he's starting to catch on.</i>

725
00:55:56,080 --> 00:55:59,280
Wow, so this is the control room.
I've been looking for it.

726
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:00,320
<i>Is there a problem?</i>

727
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:03,240
Everyone on the 23rd floor,
go check Miss Mam's office immediately.

728
00:56:03,320 --> 00:56:06,960
We're all going to get rich together!

729
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:07,960
-Rich!
-Rich!

730
00:56:08,040 --> 00:56:11,560
Rich! Rich! Rich!

731
00:56:14,080 --> 00:56:16,200
Haven't you learned anything?

732
00:56:16,880 --> 00:56:18,560
When you mess with us,

733
00:56:19,840 --> 00:56:21,760
you've got to think of everything.

734
00:57:11,000 --> 00:57:15,400
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
